cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modeling. The use of recurrent neural networks and meta-learning also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of elastic weights consolidation, which is a technique used to prevent catastrophic forgetting in neural networks, indicating that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SD (Software Engineering).
